The paper deals with time series compression, which is a common problem in databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on resource-constrained devices and the need for low memory and latency requirements suggest a connection to distributed systems (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the application of the algorithm to servers storing and querying data suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
